Title: Slow Cooker Enchilada Quinoa
Ingredients: 1 15oz can fire roasted tomatoes and green chiles
1 12 oz ball of oaxaca cheese, shredded
Directions: Add beans, corn, 1 can of enchilada sauce, dice tomatoes and chiles, quinoa, water, and cubed cream cheese to the slow cooker. Stir everything together.Pour remaining can of enchilada sauce on top, then cover with the shredded cheese. Cover and cook 4-5 hours on high or 5-7 hours on low.Uncover and top with favorite toppings.
